reviews.review_text: YES YES YES This set of three shows started of good and just kept getting better. This is an awesome performance with great Charlie Miller sound. Watch out for the enormous burst of feedback near the end of dire wolf. If your'e listening through headphones turn it down near the end of dire wolf. Foolish Heart is a disaster. Jerry couldn't remember the words hardly at all. I'm a guitar man and singer myself. I only have a list of about 30 songs I'm doing and I forget the words so I'm not too hard on him.
The sun is setting over me.. Nice sound..these LA shows were a hint of what was to come in 89'..the guests and set lists speak volumes of this show..Give It A Whirl>Forever Grateful>Forever Dead~!!!!

Guest Japanese Drummer not Id'd here? F.Y.I. Apparently, the kodo talent standing in, in addition the other well known artists you know was; Fujimoto Yoshikazu (remember Family name comes first in Japan)!

the below post is from another show. residual frog  We all had a great time. My memory of the show is a little tainted by the frog acid. Don't remember the heat. There were a few douchebags. I clearly remember Touch of Grey. We had a marvelous time.
